                .p("Two more letters were added during the Middle Ages: Օ (Oh) and Ֆ (Feh), bringing the total to 38. The original 36 are still what most Armenian primers teach as \"the alphabet,\" and you'll still see the Mashtots-era letters in old monastery inscriptions if you ever travel to Echmiadzin or Geghard."),
